[
  {
    "text": "Apple TV 4K takes the living room experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=0"
  },
  {
    "text": "to a whole new level, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=3"
  },
  {
    "text": "with support for 4K resolution, P3 color, HDR video playback, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=5"
  },
  {
    "text": "the incredible A10X Fusion processor, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=12"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the updated and improved Siri Remote. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=16"
  },
  {
    "text": "Updating your app to support these new features ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=19"
  },
  {
    "text": "is very straightforward. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=21"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first step is to add a 2x launch image. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=24"
  },
  {
    "text": "Until you do so, tvOS is going to run your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=27"
  },
  {
    "text": "in compatibility mode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=30"
  },
  {
    "text": "While you're at it, you'll also want to add 2x app icons ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=32"
  },
  {
    "text": "and top shelf images.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=35"
  },
  {
    "text": "When attached to a 4K television, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=40"
  },
  {
    "text": "UIKit will now automatically select retina assets ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=42"
  },
  {
    "text": "from your asset catalogue.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=45"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can inspect what screen scale the device is running in ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=49"
  },
  {
    "text": "by inspecting the scale property of the main UIScreen. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=52"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can also determine the pixel resolution ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=56"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the attached display by using the nativeBounds property.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=59"
  },
  {
    "text": "Just like the latest iOS and macOS devices, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=65"
  },
  {
    "text": "we're really excited that Apple TV 4K ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=68"
  },
  {
    "text": "now supports P3 color. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=71"
  },
  {
    "text": "When providing retina assets, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=73"
  },
  {
    "text": "you may also want to update your assets ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=75"
  },
  {
    "text": "to take advantage of this wider color space, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=77"
  },
  {
    "text": "allowing your graphics and images to contain ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=80"
  },
  {
    "text": "even richer and more saturated colors than before. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=82"
  },
  {
    "text": "This isn't just for flat images ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=85"
  },
  {
    "text": "but is supported for layered images as well.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=87"
  },
  {
    "text": "Media apps will also want to look at updating their streams ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=92"
  },
  {
    "text": "to include 4K and HDR variants ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=95"
  },
  {
    "text": "for any content that was produced in these formats. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=97"
  },
  {
    "text": "Apple TV 4K supports both Dolby Vision and HDR10 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=101"
  },
  {
    "text": "for HDR content, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=105"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the addition of support for HEVC ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=107"
  },
  {
    "text": "enables these higher fidelity and resolution streams ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=109"
  },
  {
    "text": "while consuming up to 40 percent less bandwidth ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=112"
  },
  {
    "text": "than comparable streams encoded using H.264.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=115"
  },
  {
    "text": "The updated and improved Siri Remote ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=119"
  },
  {
    "text": "now provides motion data for attitude and rotation rate, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=121"
  },
  {
    "text": "in addition to the values for acceleration and gravity ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=125"
  },
  {
    "text": "that the prior version offered.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=127"
  },
  {
    "text": "To determine if the paired remote ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=132"
  },
  {
    "text": "supports these new features, you can inspect the new GCMotion ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=133"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"hasAttitudeAndRotationRate\" property. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=137"
  },
  {
    "text": "The values for attitude and rotation rate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=140"
  },
  {
    "text": "are then provided by the respective GCMotion properties.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=142"
  },
  {
    "text": "And with those few changes, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=148"
  },
  {
    "text": "you're going to be able to take advantage ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=149"
  },
  {
    "text": "of all of the new capabilities and performance of Apple TV 4K.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=151"
  },
  {
    "text": "For more information on updating your app for Apple TV 4K, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=159"
  },
  {
    "text": "please visit\ndeveloper.apple.com.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-202/?time=162"
  }
]